  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2019-07-11T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "This bill requires the Department of Defense to establish a process under which the Government Accountability Office and the Inspectors General of the Departments of Homeland Security and Health and Human Services may be provided with access\u2014for purposes of conducting surprise inspections\u2014to federally-owned installations where there are facilities used to house, detain, screen, or review migrants, refugees, or other persons recently arriving in the United States."
